  "text": "Classical optimal scheduling algorithms, like Hu's algorithm [CITATION_1] and Coffman et al. 's algorithm [10] , are based on the list scheduling approach in which the nodes of the DAG are first arranged as a list such that the ordering of the nodes in the list preserves the precedence constraints. In the second step, beginning from the first node in the list, each node is removed and scheduled to a PE that allows an earliest start-time. Hereafter we refer to this second step as the start-time minimization step, which is outlined as follows.",
